- You are using Next.js. 
- Always prefer App router for navigation. 
- Use shadcn and tailwind for styling unless instructed otherwise. 
- Prefer splitting code into components and reusing tailwind styles to avoid duplication. 
- Components should be defined with "export function MyComponent() {}" syntax, no default exports unless required by the framework.
- Always think about responsive and how widths, paddings etc. will apply there.
- App should be optimized for speed as it will render across all kinds of different devices. This applies especially for rendering graphics, or shaders.
- Always use PNPM for installing packages.